# File Documentation Rule

Each file in this MetaTrader trading project must have comprehensive documentation that includes:

## Required Documentation Format
Every file must contain a header comment block at the top with the following information:

```
/*
File: [filename]
Author: [original author/creator]
Source: [where the file came from - URL, forum, purchased, etc.]
Description: [brief description of what this file does]
Purpose: [specific trading strategy/purpose]
Parameters: [list of key parameters and their purposes]
Version: [current version number]
Last Modified: [date and brief description of changes]
Compatibility: [MT4/MT5 version requirements, timeframe requirements]
*/
```

## Documentation Requirements by File Type

### Expert Advisors (EA) - .mq4/.mq5 files with OnTick()
- Strategy logic explanation
- Entry/exit conditions
- Risk management approach
- Backtesting results summary (if available)
- Recommended broker/account requirements
- Position sizing methodology

### Indicators - .mq4/.mq5 files with OnCalculate()
- Indicator calculation methodology
- Signal interpretation guidelines
- Recommended usage scenarios
- Visual display options
- Performance characteristics

### Scripts - .mq4/.mq5 files with OnStart()
- Execution purpose
- Required conditions for running
- Expected output/results
- Safety precautions

## Documentation Maintenance
- Update version and last modified date with any code changes
- Document parameter changes and their impact
- Note any compatibility issues discovered
- Include backtesting results when available
- Mark deprecated features with migration guidance

## Quality Standards
- Use clear, professional language
- Include specific parameter ranges and defaults
- Document known limitations or edge cases
- Reference external dependencies or requirements
- Include contact information for support if applicable

## Enforcement
Files without proper documentation headers will be flagged during code review and must be updated before merging.
